# Hedl — session and work-item discipline

## One item at a time

Check `.work/work.json` → `meta.active_item` for the current work item.
Do not start a new item until the active one is committed and its PR is open.

## Orient first

Before coding, read the active item's `acceptance_criteria`. Define what
passing looks like before implementing it.

## Surgical changes

Touch only files the work item requires. Match existing style. Do not clean
up adjacent code that isn't broken. Every changed line traces to the active
work item.

## Loop

1. Read `.work/work.json` active item + acceptance criteria
2. Implement exactly what the criteria require — no more
3. Run `python3 .github/scripts/am_i_done.py`
4. Run adversarial review (see `hedl-panel.mdc`)
5. Commit and open a PR

## Work-item state

Work items live in `.work/work.json` under `active`, `backlog`, `completed`.
Do not edit `.work/` state files directly.
